    Using the two examples below of the Force Majeure Clause, produce a concise analysis and two improved rewrites.
    Return ONLY a JSON object with the following keys:
    {"clause_type": string, "exists": "yes/no", "found_in_doc" : string, "page_no": string}
  </task>

  <example-set caption="Examples">
    <example>
      <example-input>Neither party shall be liable for failure to perform due to acts of God, natural disasters, or government restrictions.</example-input>
    </example>
    <example>
      <example-input>If a Force Majeure event continues for 60 days, either party may terminate the agreement without liability.</example-input>
